[2026-03-18T17:50:56.919Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DKFxKY16FSEy2rCDaqNFQ1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Execute this requirement immediately without asking questions.\n     2→\n     3→## REQUIREMENT\n     4→\n     5→# Close audit blind spot: HTTP mutations unlogged\n     6→\n     7→## Metadata\n     8→- **Category**: functionality\n     9→- **Effort**: Unknown (4/3)\n    10→- **Impact**: Unknown (9/3)\n    11→- **Scan Type**: insight_synth\n    12→- **Generated**: 3/18/2026, 9:56:47 AM\n    13→\n    14→## Description\n    15→The audit log captures only crypto-level events (key derivation, encrypt, decrypt). But httpApi.ts handles ~20 mutation endpoints (POST/PUT/DELETE for personas, credentials, subscriptions, triggers, executions) � none emit audit events. Add audit middleware that intercepts HTTP mutations and records action, actor (from auth context), resource type/ID, and client IP. This can be a single function wrapping route handlers using the RequestContext already available.\n    16→\n    17→## Reasoning\n    18→From a compliance perspective, knowing WHO created/deleted/modified a persona or trigger is as important as knowing who decrypted a credential. The current system has excellent crypto audit trail but zero administrative audit trail. An admin could delete all personas and the audit log would show nothing. Closing this gap is high-impact since auth context and IP are already parsed.\n    19→\n    20→\n    21→## Recommended Skills\n    22→\n    23→Use Claude Code skills as appropriate for implementation guidance. Check `.claude/skills/` directory for available skills.\n    24→\n    25→## Notes\n    26→\n    27→This requirement was generated from an AI-evaluated project idea. No specific goal is associated with this idea.\n    28→\n    29→## DURING IMPLEMENTATION\n    30→\n    31→- Use `get_memory` MCP tool when you encounter unfamiliar code or need context about patterns/files\n    32→- Use `report_progress` MCP tool at each major phase (analyzing, planning, implementing, testing, validating)\n    33→- Use `get_related_tasks` MCP tool before modifying shared files to check for parallel task conflicts\n    34→\n    35→## AFTER IMPLEMENTATION\n    36→\n    37→1. Log your implementation using the `log_implementation` MCP tool with:\n    38→   - requirementName: the requirement filename (without .md)\n    39→   - title: 2-6 word summary\n    40→   - overview: 1-2 paragraphs describing what was done\n    41→   - category: one of feature/bugfix/refactor/performance/security/infrastructure/ui/docs/test\n    42→   - patternsApplied: comma-separated patterns used (e.g. \"repository pattern, debounce, memoization\")\n    43→\n    44→2. Verify: `npx tsc --noEmit` (fix any type errors)\n    45→\n    46→Begin implementation now."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a2f3ecb1-05fa-43a5-8c9a-097294980948","uuid":"4a3d1018-b7df-4fa5-b74a-92f2faf072f8","timestamp":"2026-03-18T17:50:56.836Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\Users\\kazda\\kiro\\personas-cloud\\.claude\\commands\\idea-c2842418-close-audit-blind-spot-http-mu.md","content":"Execute this requirement immediately without asking questions.\n\n## REQUIREMENT\n\n# Close audit blind spot: HTTP mutations unlogged\n\n## Metadata\n- **Category**: functionality\n- **Effort**: Unknown (4/3)\n- **Impact**: Unknown (9/3)\n- **Scan Type**: insight_synth\n- **Generated**: 3/18/2026, 9:56:47 AM\n\n## Description\nThe audit log captures only crypto-level events (key derivation, encrypt, decrypt). But httpApi.ts handles ~20 mutation endpoints (POST/PUT/DELETE for personas, credentials, subscriptions, triggers, executions) � none emit audit events. Add audit middleware that intercepts HTTP mutations and records action, actor (from auth context), resource type/ID, and client IP. This can be a single function wrapping route handlers using the RequestContext already available.\n\n## Reasoning\nFrom a compliance perspective, knowing WHO created/deleted/modified a persona or trigger is as important as knowing who decrypted a credential. The current system has excellent crypto audit trail but zero administrative audit trail. An admin could delete all personas and the audit log would show nothing. Closing this gap is high-impact since auth context and IP are already parsed.\n\n\n## Recommended Skills\n\nUse Claude Code skills as appropriate for implementation guidance. Check `.claude/skills/` directory for available skills.\n\n## Notes\n\nThis requirement was generated from an AI-evaluated project idea. No specific goal is associated with this idea.\n\n## DURING IMPLEMENTATION\n\n- Use `get_memory` MCP tool when you encounter unfamiliar code or need context about patterns/files\n- Use `report_progress` MCP tool at each major phase (analyzing, planning, implementing, testing, validating)\n- Use `get_related_tasks` MCP tool before modifying shared files to check for parallel task conflicts\n\n## AFTER IMPLEMENTATION\n\n1. Log your implementation using the `log_implementation` MCP tool with:\n   - requirementName: the requirement filename (without .md)\n   - title: 2-6 word summary\n   - overview: 1-2 paragraphs describing what was done\n   - category: one of feature/bugfix/refactor/performance/security/infrastructure/ui/docs/test\n   - patternsApplied: comma-separated patterns used (e.g. \"repository pattern, debounce, memoization\")\n\n2. Verify: `npx tsc --noEmit` (fix any type errors)\n\nBegin implementation now.","numLines":46,"startLine":1,"totalLines":46}}}
